{"word":"ἕκαστος","slug":"ἕκαστος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ἕϰαστος, η, ον</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ cp.\">cp.</a> <el>ἑϰάς</el> ‘far from, far away from’] in <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ ref.\">ref.</a> to an individual <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ pers.\">pers.</a> or thing <b>each, every <a href='B:500 19:23'>J 19:23</a>; <a href='B:650 3:13'>Hb 3:13</a>;</b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ cp.\">cp.</a> <b><a href='B:490 6:44'>Lk 6:44</a>.</b> As noun <b>each one, every one <a href='B:470 16:27'>Mt 16:27</a>; <a href='B:490 13:15'>Lk 13:15</a>; <a href='B:500 6:7'>J 6:7</a>; <a href='B:520 2:6'>Ro 2:6</a>; <a href='B:650 11:21'>Hb 11:21</a>;</b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ w.\">w.</a> numeral in heightened aspect <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:εἷς\">εἷς</a> <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἕκαστος\">ἕκαστος</a></el> each one, every single one <b><a href='B:470 26:22'>Mt 26:22</a>; <a href='B:490 4:40'>Lk 4:40</a>; <a href='B:510 2:3'>Ac 2:3</a>; <a href='B:560 4:7'>Eph 4:7</a>;</b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ sim.\">sim.</a> <b><a href='B:730 21:21'>Rv 21:21</a></b> (where <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἀνά\">ἀνά</a></el> is adverbial). <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:ἐκ\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ἑκάστοτε\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}